-- Turkey Stocks: Ford Otomotiv, Koc Holding, Halkbank Were Active
-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 2012-01-11T16:11:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-11/turkey-stocks-ford-otomotiv-gozde-girisim-halkbank-are-active.html
Turkey ’s benchmark  ISE National 100
Index  gained for a second day, rising 1.2 percent to 51,410.44
at the close in Istanbul.  The following were among the active equities in the Turkish
market today. Stock symbols are in parentheses.  Ford Otomotiv Sanayi AS (FROTO)  , Ford Motor Co.’s unit
in Turkey, climbed 2.7 percent to 15.50 liras, rising for a
third day. The company is considering passenger car production
at its Turkish factory, Hurriyet newspaper said, citing Ford
Executive Chairman  Bill Ford .  Koc Holding AS (KCHOL)  , Turkey’s largest industrial
company, increased 1.3 percent to 6.04 liras. The group’s fuel
retailer, Opet Petrolculuk, recorded 14.8 billion liras ($8
billion) in sales last year, according to a press release today.  Turkiye Halk Bankasi AS (HALKB)  , a state-run bank,
gained 1.7 percent to 9.78 liras. The bank said it hasn’t
received any request to stop its oil payments to Iran, according
to a report in Vatan newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Harvey in Istanbul at 
